Hai District Commissioner, Lengai Ole Sabaya has issued District Personnel Department with three days ultimatum to present him with detailed information, explaining what is blocking documents of retired teachers from being sent to the General Secretary of the Treasury, two years now down the road. Ole Sabaya said this on Tuesday evening stressing that the government can not lack money to pay the retired teacher. However, he blamed the department of personnel for negligence, adding that that is causing unnecessary dispute between the government and its employees. Elaborating, the DC ordered that within the notice period, he wants letters to be written to all the affected teachers and their claims approved, adding that his office will spearhead the exercise and see into it that they get their rights.